{
  "title": "Oversmack",
  "children": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "lines": [
        "Smack with the whole",
        "Move surface as a",
        "step-FX editor.",
        "",
        "Reads the mic or",
        "line input directly",
        "and keeps running",
        "while suspended.",
        "",
        "Open it from the",
        "overtake menu",
        "(Shift+Vol+Jog).",
        "Back hides the UI;",
        "audio keeps going.",
        "Shift+Vol+Jog exits."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Quick Start",
      "lines": [
        "1. Set Loop Len.",
        "2. Play something",
        " into mic/line in.",
        "3. Hit Capture to",
        " grab the last",
        " loop length.",
        "4. Press a step,",
        " then tap a pad in",
        " the upper rows to",
        " set its effect.",
        "5. Re-Roll for a",
        " new random",
        " pattern; edits",
        " stay locked."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Grid",
      "lines": [
        "Steps 1-16: the",
        "slice pattern, one",
        "color per effect,",
        "white is playhead.",
        "Press to select a",
        "slice for editing",
        "(shown green).",
        "",
        "Upper 3 pad rows:",
        "effect palette.",
        "Row 2 left = Clean,",
        "then the 22 FX in",
        "engine order.",
        "Top-right pad =",
        "Unlock (back to",
        "the seeded roll).",
        "",
        "Bottom row:",
        "Capture, Arm, A/B,",
        "Re-Roll, Clear,",
        "Fill (tap=latch,",
        "hold=momentary).",
        "",
        "Play button still",
        "controls Move."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Knobs",
      "lines": [
        "1: FX Density",
        "2: Order Density",
        "3: Loop Length",
        "4: Slice Res",
        "5: Wet",
        "6: Pitch Range",
        "7: Fill Amount",
        "8: Seed",
        "",
        "Quantize is on the",
        "hierarchy Setup",
        "page."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Editing & Locks",
      "lines": [
        "Tapping a palette",
        "pad pins that",
        "effect to the",
        "selected slice.",
        "Pinned slices keep",
        "their effect when",
        "you Re-Roll.",
        "",
        "Tap the same",
        "effect again to",
        "lock the current",
        "rolled flavor.",
        "Unlock returns the",
        "slice to the",
        "seeded pattern."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Fill",
      "lines": [
        "Fill is a temporary",
        "pattern variation,",
        "like Elektron fills.",
        "",
        "A second seeded",
        "pattern, biased",
        "toward stutters,",
        "sounds only while",
        "Fill is on; the",
        "main pattern is the",
        "\"not fill\" side.",
        "",
        "Fill pad (yellow):",
        "tap latches Fill,",
        "tap again to stop;",
        "hold plays it only",
        "while held.",
        "",
        "Fill knob page:",
        "Fill: on/off latch.",
        "Fill 1x: fill to",
        "the end of this",
        "pass, then off.",
        "Fill Amt: how busy",
        "the fill gets.",
        "",
        "Fill works over the",
        "A side too, and",
        "follows Quantize.",
        "Re-Roll and Seed",
        "change the fill",
        "pattern with the",
        "main one."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Seed & Re-Roll",
      "lines": [
        "Seed browses",
        "patterns by number:",
        "the same seed always",
        "gives the same",
        "pattern.",
        "",
        "Re-Roll varies the",
        "current seed for a",
        "fresh pattern; dial",
        "the Seed knob to",
        "return to the",
        "canonical one."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Sync & Transport",
      "lines": [
        "Set Move's MIDI",
        "Clock to Out so",
        "the loop locks to",
        "the transport.",
        "",
        "Without it, the",
        "loop free-runs at",
        "the project tempo.",
        "",
        "The Play button is",
        "passed through to",
        "Move, so transport",
        "and clock work",
        "under this UI."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Screen Reader",
      "lines": [
        "With the screen",
        "reader on (Global",
        "Settings), steps,",
        "pads, knob changes",
        "and loop state are",
        "all announced."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
